         <notesStmt>
            <note type="summary">1. Z. had been travelling but was delayed in Mantua,
                            because his community pleaded with him not to leave, because his wife
                            had become sick with boils and because the community of Alessandria had
                            sent him R. Abraham Katz to ask Z. that he may talk to Rovigo regarding
                            the separation (?) between him and his brother R. Benjamin Katz.He adds
                            personal reasons, the ?? of his wife and the young age of his daughter.
                            2. Z. reports news he read in a letter from Venice: the sea is full of
                            pirates who have recently plundered several English ships. 3. Z.
                            implores Rovigo that he may take the matter of Eleazar Norzi into his
                            hands. Who has several legal cases with his brother in Modena that
                            prevent his betrothal. He asks Rovigo to intercede with R. Abraham
                            Graziano in this matter.</note>
            <note type="incipit" xml:lang="he">בזאת ידעתי כי תשמח
